            <a:r>
              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>RagExecutionHints is the control plane for adaptive RAG. research_profile drives which strategy to use: corpus_discovery switches to broad semantic sweeps, comparison_campaign triggers side-by-side clause extraction, process_flow_identification prefers process_flow or clause chunks. coverage_goal controls breadth: corpus_wide means everywhere, targeted means the most relevant doc. result_mode controls output format: inventory returns a structured list, comparison_table structures side-by-side. controller_hints is the escape valve: force_keyword_only disables vectors, disable_judge_grading skips the slow LLM step, max_rounds overrides the limit. Three sources merge: explicit hints win, then skill-driven hints, then heuristic inference. merge_rag_execution_hints() fills blanks from lower-priority sources.</a:t>
            </a:r>
          </a:p>
